I recognized you as Colonel Mustard.


1019
01:08:46.749 --> 01:08:48.001
And I prevented you
from telling me your real name


1020
01:08:48.084 --> 01:08:50.587
because I didn't want any of you to use
any name other than your pseudonym.


1021
01:08:50.670 --> 01:08:51.671
And I introduced myself to you
as a butler,


1022
01:08:51.754 --> 01:08:53.756
and I made across
the hall to the library.

1023
01:08:55.424 --> 01:08:59.474
And then Yvette met you and smiled
and poured you a drink.


1024
01:09:02.181 --> 01:09:03.353
And the doorbell rang.

1025
01:09:03.432 --> 01:09:05.059
And it was Mrs. White
looking pale and tragic.


1026
01:09:05.142 --> 01:09:07.110
And I took her
coat and hung it up.

1027
01:09:08.396 --> 01:09:10.694
And I introduced Mrs. White
to Colonel Mustard.


1028
01:09:10.773 --> 01:09:12.195
"Hello." "Hello."

1029
01:09:12.275 --> 01:09:15.279
And I noticed that Mrs. White
and Yvette flinched.


1030
01:09:15.361 --> 01:09:18.456
Then there was a rumble of thunder
and a crash of lightning.


1031
01:09:19.615 --> 01:09:21.743
- And to make a long story short...
- Too late!


1032
01:09:21.826 --> 01:09:23.624
One by one you all arrived.

1033
01:09:23.744 --> 01:09:25.621
And then the gong was struck
by the cook.


1034
01:09:25.705 --> 01:09:28.299
And we went into the dining room.

1035
01:09:30.376 --> 01:09:32.925
And Mrs. Peacock sat here.
And Professor Plum sat here.


1036
01:09:33.004 --> 01:09:34.130
Mrs. White sat here.

1037
01:09:34.213 --> 01:09:36.307
Mr. Green, Miss Scarlet,
Colonel Mustard.


1038
01:09:36.382 --> 01:09:37.554
This chair was vacant.

1039
01:09:37.633 --> 01:09:39.931
Anyway, we all revealed
we'd all received a letter.


1040
01:09:40.011 --> 01:09:41.729
You had a letter, and you had a letter,
and you had a letter.


1041
01:09:41.804 --> 01:09:42.851
Get on with it!

1042
01:09:42.930 --> 01:09:44.898
The point is... Blackmail!

1043
01:09:44.974 --> 01:09:47.397
All this came out after dinner
in the study.


1044
01:09:47.476 --> 01:09:48.819
You're right!

1045
01:09:51.856 --> 01:09:53.574
Mr. Green stood here.

1046
01:09:53.649 --> 01:09:55.071
And Mrs. Peacock here.

1047
01:09:55.151 --> 01:09:56.778
And Miss Scarlet here.
Professor Plum here.


1048
01:09:56.861 --> 01:09:58.408
And Colonel Mustard and Mrs. White.

1049
01:09:58.487 --> 01:10:00.910
- Get on with it!
- I'm getting there, I'm getting there.


1050
01:10:00.990 --> 01:10:03.084
And Mr. Boddy went to get
the surprise packages from the hall.


1051
01:10:03.159 --> 01:10:05.161
And you all opened your presents.

1052
01:10:05.870 --> 01:10:07.998
Mr. Boddy switched off the lights.

1053
01:10:14.545 --> 01:10:16.593
Grand.

1054
01:10:16.672 --> 01:10:19.425
Mr. Boddy lay on the floor
apparently dead.


1055
01:10:19.508 --> 01:10:20.851
He was dead! I examined him.

1056
01:10:20.927 --> 01:10:22.895
Then why was he bashed on the head
a few minutes later with a candlestick


1057
01:10:22.970 --> 01:10:23.937
if he was dead already?

1058
01:10:24.013 --> 01:10:25.481
All right, I made a mistake.

1059
01:10:25.556 --> 01:10:28.810
Right, but if so, why was Mr. Boddy
pretending to be dead?


1060
01:10:28.893 --> 01:10:32.397
It could only be 'cause he realized
his scheme had misfired,


1061
01:10:32.480 --> 01:10:34.778
and the gunshot was intended
to kill him, not me.


1062
01:10:34.857 --> 01:10:37.781
Look. The bullet grazed his ear.

1063
01:10:37.860 --> 01:10:40.955
Clearly his best hope of escaping death
was to pretend to be dead already.


1064
01:10:41.030 --> 01:10:43.408
Whoever tried to grab the gun from me
in the dark was trying to kill him.


1065
01:10:43.491 --> 01:10:45.368
But remember what happened next.

1066
01:10:45.451 --> 01:10:47.874
Mrs. Peacock took a drink.

1067
01:10:47.954 --> 01:10:49.877
You said, "Maybe it's poisoned."

1068
01:10:49.956 --> 01:10:51.378
She screams. "Aah!"

1069
01:10:51.457 --> 01:10:54.381
We took her to the sofa.

1070
01:10:54.460 --> 01:10:55.962
Mr. Green...

1071
01:10:56.963 --> 01:10:59.887
"Well, I had to stop her screaming."

1072
01:10:59.966 --> 01:11:01.468
Then, more screaming.

1073
01:11:01.550 --> 01:11:02.893
Yvette! The billiard room!

1074
01:11:02.969 --> 01:11:04.312
We all rushed out.

1075
01:11:06.722 --> 01:11:09.350
But one of us wasn't here. No.

1076
01:11:09.433 --> 01:11:11.185
- No?
- No?


1077
01:11:11.268 --> 01:11:12.895
Maybe one of us
was murdering the cook.


1078
01:11:12.979 --> 01:11:14.526
Who wasn't here with us?

1079
01:11:15.982 --> 01:11:17.700
- Do you know?
- I do.


1080
01:11:18.067 --> 01:11:19.284
While we stood here,

1081
01:11:19.360 --> 01:11:21.658
trying to stop Yvette from panicking,

1082
01:11:21.737 --> 01:11:23.705
one of us could have
stayed in the study,


1083
01:11:23.781 --> 01:11:25.033
picked up the dagger,

1084
01:11:25.116 --> 01:11:27.869
run down the hall,

1085
01:11:27.952 --> 01:11:29.499
and stabbed the cook!

1086
01:11:29.578 --> 01:11:32.502
How could he risk it?
We might've seen him running back.


1087
01:11:32.581 --> 01:11:34.800
Not if they used this secret passage.

1088
01:11:35.918 --> 01:11:38.637
And the murdered ran back
down the secret passage to the study.


1089
01:11:38.713 --> 01:11:40.465
That's where it comes out?

1090
01:11:40.548 --> 01:11:41.595
WADSWORTH1 Yes! Look!

1091
01:11:43.467 --> 01:11:44.468
What?

1092
01:11:44.552 --> 01:11:45.895
How did you know?

1093
01:11:45.970 --> 01:11:48.018
This house belongs to a friend of mine.
I've known all along.


1094
01:11:48.097 --> 01:11:49.349
So you could be the murderer.

1095
01:11:49.432 --> 01:11:51.685
Don't be ridiculous.
If I was the murderer,


1096
01:11:51.767 --> 01:11:53.235
would I reveal to
you how I did it?

1097
01:11:54.812 --> 01:11:56.985
Well, who else knew
about the secret passage?


1098
01:11:57.064 --> 01:11:58.987
We found it, Colonel Mustard and me.

1099
01:11:59.066 --> 01:12:00.818
You found it. You could've known
about it all the time.


1100
01:12:00.901 --> 01:12:01.993
But I didn't.

1101
01:12:02.069 --> 01:12:03.412
Well, why should we believe you?

1102
01:12:03.529 --> 01:12:05.531
Because she was with us all
in the billiard room doorway


1103
01:12:05.614 --> 01:12:07.537
while Yvette was screaming,
don't you remember?


1104
01:12:07.616 --> 01:12:08.708
But what I don't understand is

1105
01:12:08.784 --> 01:12:12.129
why was the cook murdered?
She had nothing to do with Mr. Boddy.


1106
01:12:12.204 --> 01:12:13.706
Of course she did.

1107
01:12:13.789 --> 01:12:15.211
I gathered you all here together

1108
01:12:15.291 --> 01:12:18.716
because you were all implicated
in Mr. Boddy's dastardly blackmail.


1109
01:12:18.794 --> 01:12:21.968
Did none of you deduce
the others were involved, too?


1110
01:12:23.090 --> 01:12:25.218
- What others?
- The cook and Yvette.


1111
01:12:25.301 --> 01:12:26.393
No.

1112
01:12:26.469 --> 01:12:28.892
That's how he got all his information.

1113
01:12:28.971 --> 01:12:30.894
Before he could blackmail anyone,

1114
01:12:30.973 --> 01:12:33.396
Mr. Boddy had to discover
their guilty secret.


1115
01:12:33.476 --> 01:12:35.695
The cook and Yvette
were his accomplices.


1116
01:12:35.770 --> 01:12:37.022
I see.

1117
01:12:37.104 --> 01:12:39.482
So whoever knew

1118
01:12:39.565 --> 01:12:42.614
that the cook was involved killed her?

1119
01:12:42.693 --> 01:12:43.945
Yes.

1120
01:12:45.029 --> 01:12:48.124
I know, because I was
Mr. Boddy's butler,


1121
01:12:48.199 --> 01:12:50.042
that the cook had
worked for one of you.

1122
01:12:50.117 --> 01:12:51.209
Who?

1123
01:12:51.285 --> 01:12:52.537
You recognized Yvette, didn't you?

1124
01:12:52.620 --> 01:12:53.917
Don't deny it.

1125
01:12:53.996 --> 01:12:55.418
What do you mean don't deny it?

1126
01:12:55.498 --> 01:12:56.920
I'm not denying anything.

1127
01:12:56.999 --> 01:12:58.251
Another denial.

1128
01:12:58.334 --> 01:13:01.133
All right, it's true, 
I knew Yvette.

1129
01:13:01.212 --> 01:13:04.807
My husband had an affair with her,
but I didn't care, I wasn't jealous.


1130
01:13:04.882 --> 01:13:06.304
You knew Yvette, too, didn't you?

1131
01:13:06.383 --> 01:13:07.635
Yes. She worked for me.

1132
01:13:07.718 --> 01:13:08.970
And you also knew her, sir.

1133
01:13:09.053 --> 01:13:10.396
We've already established

1134
01:13:10.471 --> 01:13:12.894
that you were one
of Miss Scarlet's clients.


1135
01:13:12.973 --> 01:13:15.226
That's why you were so desperate
to get your hands on those negatives,


1136
01:13:15.309 --> 01:13:18.859
photographs of you and Yvette
in ?agrante delicto, remember?


1137
01:13:19.021 --> 01:13:22.525
Mr. Boddy threatened to send
those pictures to my dear old mother,


1138
01:13:22.608 --> 01:13:24.030
the shock would've killed her.

1139
01:13:24.110 --> 01:13:25.828
That would've been
quite an achievement,


1140
01:13:25.903 --> 01:13:27.871
since you told us that
she's dead already.


1141
01:13:27.947 --> 01:13:29.290
So, he had the motive.

1142
01:13:29.365 --> 01:13:30.867
You all had a motive.

1143
01:13:30.950 --> 01:13:32.998
But where and when
was Mr. Boddy killed?


1144
01:13:33.077 --> 01:13:35.455
Don't you see? Look.

1145
01:13:35.538 --> 01:13:37.131
We came back to the study with Yvette.

1146
01:13:37.206 --> 01:13:39.629
Mr. Boddy was on the floor,
pretending to be dead,


1147
01:13:39.708 --> 01:13:41.460
but one of us knows he's alive.

1148
01:13:41.544 --> 01:13:44.468
So I explained that I was Mr. Boddy's
butler and I'd invited you here.


1149
01:13:44.547 --> 01:13:47.016
And we realized there was only
one other person in the house.


1150
01:13:47.091 --> 01:13:48.468
The cook!

1151
01:13:56.475 --> 01:13:58.898
Well, where is he?

1152
01:14:05.067 --> 01:14:06.319
By now she was dead.

1153
01:14:06.402 --> 01:14:08.200
We laid her down
with our backs to the freezer.


1154
01:14:08.404 --> 01:14:11.157
One of us slipped through
the same secret passage.


1155
01:14:11.240 --> 01:14:12.332
Again?

1156
01:14:12.408 --> 01:14:14.877
Of course. Back to the study.

1157
01:14:14.952 --> 01:14:16.875
The murderer was in
the secret passage.


1158
01:14:16.954 --> 01:14:19.753
Meanwhile, Mr. Boddy
had been on the floor.


1159
01:14:19.915 --> 01:14:21.337
He jumped UP.

1160
01:14:21.417 --> 01:14:24.011
The murderer came out of
the secret panel,


1161
01:14:24.086 --> 01:14:26.430
picked up the candlestick.

1162
01:14:26.505 --> 01:14:29.224
Mr. Boddy followed us out of the study
and into the hall looking for an escape.


1163
01:14:29.300 --> 01:14:32.019
The murderer crept up behind him
and killed him!


1164
01:14:33.637 --> 01:14:35.560
Will you stop that?

1165
01:14:35.639 --> 01:14:37.312
No.

1166
01:14:37.391 --> 01:14:40.235
Then he threw him into the toilet

1167
01:14:40.311 --> 01:14:42.905
and nonchalantly rejoined us
besides the cook's body in the kitchen.


1168
01:14:42.980 --> 01:14:44.027
It took less than half a minute.

1169
01:14:44.106 --> 01:14:45.904
So who wasn't there
the entire time in the kitchen?


1170
01:14:45.983 --> 01:14:47.405
Whoever it was is the murderer.

1171
01:14:51.530 --> 01:14:53.373
And we put the weapons
in the cupboard


1172
01:14:53.449 --> 01:14:55.622
locked it, and ran to the front door

1173
01:14:55.743 --> 01:14:58.246
to throw away the key.

1174
01:14:58.329 --> 01:15:00.548
The motorist!

1175
01:15:00.623 --> 01:15:02.876
I didn't throw it. 
I put it in my pocket.

1176
01:15:02.958 --> 01:15:05.381
And someone could've taken it out of
my pocket and substituted another.


1177
01:15:05.461 --> 01:15:06.883
We were all in a huddle.

1178
01:15:06.962 --> 01:15:09.340
- Anyone of us could've done that.
- Precisely.


1179
01:15:09.465 --> 01:15:10.967
Wait a minute.

1180
01:15:12.301 --> 01:15:15.601
Colonel Mustard
has a top-secret Pentagon job.


1181
01:15:15.679 --> 01:15:19.058
Mrs. White's husband was
a nuclear physicist, and...


1182
01:15:20.476 --> 01:15:23.946
Yvette is a link between them.

1183
01:15:24.021 --> 01:15:25.989
What's your top-secret job, Colonel?

1184
01:15:26.065 --> 01:15:29.615
I can tell you. He's working on
the secret of the next fusion bomb.


1185
01:15:30.819 --> 01:15:32.071
How did you know that?

1186
01:15:32.154 --> 01:15:35.078
- Can you keep a secret? So can I.
- Yeah.


1187
01:15:35.157 --> 01:15:38.627
Is this a plot between them, Wadsworth,
or did Colonel Mustard do it alone?


1188
01:15:38.702 --> 01:15:40.830
We shall see.
Let's look at the other murders.


1189
01:15:40.913 --> 01:15:43.416
Yes. Bad luck that motorist
arrived at that moment.


1190
01:15:43.499 --> 01:15:45.593
It wasn't luck. 
I invited him.

1191
01:15:45.668 --> 01:15:48.046
- You did?
- Of course, it's obvious.


1192
01:15:48.128 --> 01:15:50.927
Everyone here tonight was either
Mr. Boddy's victim or accomplice.


1193
01:15:51.006 --> 01:15:54.727
Everyone who's died gave him
vital information about one of you.


1194
01:15:54.802 --> 01:15:57.146
I got them here
so they'd give evidence against him


1195
01:15:57.221 --> 01:15:58.268
and force him to confess.

1196
01:15:58.347 --> 01:15:59.894
Yeah? What about that motorist?

1197
01:15:59.974 --> 01:16:01.692
What kind of information did he have?

1198
01:16:02.393 --> 01:16:04.691
He was my driver during the war.

1199
01:16:05.104 --> 01:16:07.198
And what was he holding over you?

1200
01:16:08.023 --> 01:16:10.697
He knew that I was a war profiteer.

1201
01:16:12.653 --> 01:16:17.910
I stole essential air force radio parts,
and I sold them on the black market.


1202
01:16:17.992 --> 01:16:19.710
That's how I made all my money.

1203
01:16:20.327 --> 01:16:22.295
But that doesn't make me a murderer.

1204
01:16:22.371 --> 01:16:24.419
Well, a lot of our airmen died

1205
01:16:24.498 --> 01:16:26.626
because their radios didn't work.

1206
01:16:26.709 --> 01:16:29.633
Was the policeman working
for Mr. Boddy, too?


1207
01:16:29.712 --> 01:16:31.464
The cop was from Washington.

1208
01:16:31.547 --> 01:16:32.844
He was on my payroll.

1209
01:16:32.923 --> 01:16:35.551
I bribed him once a week
so I could carry on with business.


1210
01:16:35.801 --> 01:16:37.974
Mr. Boddy found out somehow.

1211
01:16:38.053 --> 01:16:39.475
My God!

1212
01:16:39.555 --> 01:16:41.307
Please.

1213
01:16:42.433 --> 01:16:44.561
And the singing telegram girl?

1214
01:16:48.397 --> 01:16:50.525
She was my patient once.

1215
01:16:50.941 --> 01:16:53.194
I had an affair with her.

1216
01:16:53.277 --> 01:16:54.904
That's how I lost my license.

1217
01:16:54.987 --> 01:16:57.240
Mr. Boddy found that out, too.

1218
01:16:57.948 --> 01:17:01.293
Well, let's put her in the study
with the others.


1219
01:17:03.412 --> 01:17:06.882
So, now you all know why they died.

1220
01:17:06.957 --> 01:17:10.962
Whoever killed Mr. Boddy
also wanted his accomplices dead.


1221
01:17:11.045 --> 01:17:12.922
How did the murderer
know about them all?


1222
01:17:13.255 --> 01:17:14.472
I mean I admit

1223
01:17:14.548 --> 01:17:17.518
that I'd guessed that this young singer
informed on me to Mr. Boddy.


1224
01:17:17.593 --> 01:17:20.517
But I didn't know anything
about any of you until this evening.


1225
01:17:20.596 --> 01:17:23.520
First, the murderer needed
to get the weapons. Easy.


1226
01:17:23.599 --> 01:17:26.022
He stole the key from my pocket.

1227
01:17:26.143 --> 01:17:27.941
And then we all followed
Colonel Mustard's suggestion


1228
01:17:28.020 --> 01:17:29.693
that we split up and search the house.

1229
01:17:29.772 --> 01:17:31.149
That's right.

1230
01:17:31.231 --> 01:17:32.983
It was Colonel Mustard's suggestion.

1231
01:17:33.067 --> 01:17:35.195
And one of us got away
from his or her partner


1232
01:17:35.277 --> 01:17:37.120
and hurried to the study.

1233
01:17:37.196 --> 01:17:39.449
On the desk was the envelope
from Mr. Boddy.


1234
01:17:39.531 --> 01:17:41.078
It contained photographs and letters,

1235
01:17:41.158 --> 01:17:43.911
the evidence of Mr. Boddy's
network of informants.


1236
01:17:43.994 --> 01:17:45.291
Where is the envelope now?

1237
01:17:45.371 --> 01:17:46.463
Gone.

1238
01:17:48.082 --> 01:17:49.800
Destroyed.

1239
01:17:49.875 --> 01:17:51.297
Perhaps in the fire.

1240
01:17:51.377 --> 01:17:52.970
The only possible place.

1241
01:17:54.922 --> 01:17:56.014
Aha!

1242
01:17:57.091 --> 01:17:58.968
Then, having found out the whole story,

1243
01:17:59.051 --> 01:18:01.395
the murderer went to the cupboard,

1244
01:18:01.470 --> 01:18:03.143
unlocked it with the key,
took out the wrench...


1245
01:18:03.305 --> 01:18:06.605
Then we found the secret passage
from the conservatory to the lounge,


1246
01:18:06.683 --> 01:18:08.435
where we found the motorist dead.

1247
01:18:08.519 --> 01:18:10.442
That's right. And we couldn't get in.

1248
01:18:10.521 --> 01:18:12.239
So Yvette ran to the open cupboard,

1249
01:18:12.314 --> 01:18:15.443
got the gun, and shot the door open.
Bang!


1250
01:18:15.526 --> 01:18:16.743
And then the doorbell rang.

1251
01:18:19.530 --> 01:18:22.033
Whoever it is, they've got to go away,

1252
01:18:22.116 --> 01:18:24.039
or they'll be killed.

1253
01:18:26.120 --> 01:18:30.296
Good evening. Have you ever given any
thought to the kingdom of heaven?


1254
01:18:30.374 --> 01:18:31.421
What?

1255
01:18:31.500 --> 01:18:34.424
Repent.
The kingdom of heaven is at hand.


1256
01:18:34.503 --> 01:18:35.925
You ain't whistling Dixie.

1257
01:18:36.004 --> 01:18:38.098
Armageddon is almost upon us.

1258
01:18:38.173 --> 01:18:39.550
I got news for you. 
It's already here.

1259
01:18:39.633 --> 01:18:40.885
Go away!

1260
01:18:40.968 --> 01:18:42.936
But your souls are in danger.

1261
01:18:43.011 --> 01:18:44.888
Our lives are in danger, you beatnik!

1262
01:18:46.473 --> 01:18:47.725
The cop arrived next.

1263
01:18:47.808 --> 01:18:49.060
We locked him in the library.

1264
01:18:49.143 --> 01:18:51.020
We forgot the cupboard with
the weapons was now unlocked.


1265
01:18:51.103 --> 01:18:52.446
Then we split up again,

1266
01:18:52.521 --> 01:18:55.274
and the murderer switched off
the electricity.


1267
01:18:55.399 --> 01:18:56.651
My God!

1268
01:18:56.733 --> 01:18:57.825
Not again.

1269
01:18:57.901 --> 01:18:58.902
Turn on the lights!

1270
01:19:00.195 --> 01:19:02.197
Sorry. Didn't mean to frighten you.

1271
01:19:02.281 --> 01:19:04.124
You're a bit late for that!

1272
01:19:04.199 --> 01:19:06.076
I hate when he does that.

1273
01:19:06.160 --> 01:19:08.128
Then there were three more murders.

1274
01:19:08.203 --> 01:19:09.375
So which of us killed them?

1275
01:19:09.455 --> 01:19:11.378
None of us killed Mr. 
Boddy or the cook.

1276
01:19:11.457 --> 01:19:12.504
So who did?

1277
01:19:12.583 --> 01:19:15.052
The one person who wasn't with us.

1278
01:19:16.712 --> 01:19:17.713
Yvette.

1279
01:19:17.796 --> 01:19:19.264
- Yvette?
- Yvette?


1280
01:19:19.339 --> 01:19:22.138
She was in the billiards room
listening to our conversation.


1281
01:19:22.217 --> 01:19:24.219
She heard the gunshot.
She thought he was dead.


1282
01:19:24.303 --> 01:19:25.976
And while we all
examined the bullet hole,


1283
01:19:26.054 --> 01:19:29.058
she crept into the study,
picked up the dagger, ran to the kitchen,


1284
01:19:29.141 --> 01:19:30.393
and stabbed the cook.

1285
01:19:30.476 --> 01:19:31.819
We didn't hear the cook scream

1286
01:19:31.894 --> 01:19:34.693
because Mrs. Peacock was screaming
about the poisoned brandy.


1287
01:19:34.771 --> 01:19:36.398
Then Yvette returned
to the billiard room.


1288
01:19:36.482 --> 01:19:38.325
She screamed, and we all ran to her.

1289
01:19:38.400 --> 01:19:39.993
When did she kill Mr. Boddy?

1290
01:19:40.068 --> 01:19:41.320
When I said.

1291
01:19:41.403 --> 01:19:43.326
We all ran to the kitchen
to see the cook.


1292
01:19:43.405 --> 01:19:45.828
Yvette hid in the study
to check that Mr. Boddy was dead.


1293
01:19:45.908 --> 01:19:48.286
He got up and followed them
down the hall.


1294
01:19:48.368 --> 01:19:50.791
So she hit him on the head
with the candlestick,


1295
01:19:50.871 --> 01:19:52.464
and dragged him to the toilet.

1296
01:19:52.539 --> 01:19:53.540
Why?

1297
01:19:53.624 --> 01:19:54.876
To create confusion.

1298
01:19:54.958 --> 01:19:56.835
It worked.

1299
01:19:56.919 --> 01:19:57.920
Why did she do it?

1300
01:19:58.003 --> 01:20:00.256
Was it because
she was acting under orders


1301
01:20:00.339 --> 01:20:02.262
from the person who later killed her?

1302
01:20:02.341 --> 01:20:03.718
- Who?
'Who?


1303
01:20:03.884 --> 01:20:04.976
Who?

1304
01:20:05.802 --> 01:20:08.806
Was it one of her clients?

1305
01:20:09.389 --> 01:20:11.812
Or was it a jealous wife?

1306
01:20:11.892 --> 01:20:13.815
Or an adulterous doctor?

1307
01:20:14.645 --> 01:20:15.862
No.

1308
01:20:15.938 --> 01:20:18.361
It was her employer, Miss Scarlet.

1309
01:20:18.440 --> 01:20:19.692
That's a lie!

1310
01:20:19.775 --> 01:20:21.197
Is it?

1311
01:20:21.276 --> 01:20:24.029
You used her
the way you always used her.


1312
01:20:24.112 --> 01:20:26.706
You killed the motorist
when we split up to search the house.


1313
01:20:26.782 --> 01:20:28.750
How could I have known
about the secret passage?


1314
01:20:28.825 --> 01:20:30.668
Easy. Yvette told you.

1315
01:20:30.953 --> 01:20:34.548
So when we split up again,
you switched off the electricity.


1316
01:20:34.623 --> 01:20:36.546
It was easy for you
here on the ground ?oor.


1317
01:20:36.625 --> 01:20:40.880
Then, in the dark, you got the lead pipe,
and the rope, strangled Yvette,


1318
01:20:40.963 --> 01:20:43.386
ran to the library, killed the cop,

1319
01:20:43.465 --> 01:20:46.264
picked up the gun
where Yvette dropped it,


1320
01:20:46.343 --> 01:20:47.936
opened the front door,

1321
01:20:48.011 --> 01:20:50.855
recognized the singing telegram
from her photograph,


1322
01:20:50.931 --> 01:20:52.433
and shot her.

1323
01:20:53.100 --> 01:20:54.317
You've no proof.

1324
01:20:54.393 --> 01:20:55.770
The gun is missing.

1325
01:20:55.852 --> 01:20:57.775
Gentlemen, turn out your pockets.

1326
01:20:57.854 --> 01:20:59.652
Ladies, empty your purses.

1327
01:21:00.524 --> 01:21:04.074
Whoever has the gun is the murderer.

1328
01:21:04.152 --> 01:21:05.654
Brilliantly worked out, Wadsworth.

1329
01:21:05.737 --> 01:21:06.989
I congratulate you.

1330
01:21:07.114 --> 01:21:08.240
Me, too.

1331
01:21:08.323 --> 01:21:09.620
Shut Up!

1332
01:21:09.825 --> 01:21:11.668
Now there's one thing
I don't understand.


1333
01:21:11.743 --> 01:21:12.915
One thing?

1334
01:21:12.995 --> 01:21:14.087
Why did you do it?

1335
01:21:14.162 --> 01:21:16.381
Half of Washington knows
what kind of business you run.


1336
01:21:16.582 --> 01:21:18.755
You were in no real danger.

1337
01:21:18.834 --> 01:21:20.928
The whole town would be implicated
if you were exposed.


1338
01:21:21.003 --> 01:21:23.426
I don't think they know my real business.

1339
01:21:23.505 --> 01:21:25.428
My business is secrets.

1340
01:21:25.507 --> 01:21:28.431
Yvette found them out for me.

1341
01:21:28.510 --> 01:21:31.434
The secrets of Senator Peacock's
defense committee,


1342
01:21:31.513 --> 01:21:34.813
of Colonel Mustard's fusion bomb,

1343
01:21:34.891 --> 01:21:37.314
Professor Plum's UN contacts,

1344
01:21:38.061 --> 01:21:40.530
and the work of your husband,

1345
01:21:40.606 --> 01:21:43.450
the nuclear physicist.

1346
01:21:44.109 --> 01:21:45.907
So, it is political.

1347
01:21:45.986 --> 01:21:47.329
You're a communist!

1348
01:21:47.404 --> 01:21:50.874
No, Mr. Green,
communism is just a red herring.


1349
01:21:51.575 --> 01:21:53.168
Like all members
of the oldest profession,


1350
01:21:53.243 --> 01:21:54.540
I'm a capitalist,

1351
01:21:54.620 --> 01:21:56.748
and I'm gonna sell my secrets,

1352
01:21:56.830 --> 01:21:58.252
your secrets,

1353
01:21:58.332 --> 01:22:00.005
to the highest bidder.

1354
01:22:00.083 --> 01:22:02.381
What if we don't cooperate?

1355
01:22:02.461 --> 01:22:05.180
You will, or I'll expose you.

1356
01:22:05.255 --> 01:22:07.223
We could expose you. Six murders?

1357
01:22:07.299 --> 01:22:10.599
I hardly think it will enhance your
reputation at the UN, Professor Plum,


1358
01:22:10.677 --> 01:22:12.930
if it's revealed that
you've been implicated


1359
01:22:13.013 --> 01:22:14.936
not only in adultery
with one of your patients


1360
01:22:15.015 --> 01:22:18.610
but in her death
and the deaths of five other people.


1361
01:22:18.685 --> 01:22:20.153
You don't know what kind of people
they have at the UN.


1362
01:22:20.228 --> 01:22:21.571
I might go up in their estimation.

1363
01:22:21.647 --> 01:22:24.901
And it's no good
blackmailing me, madam.


1364
01:22:24.983 --> 01:22:26.235
I have no more money.

1365
01:22:26.318 --> 01:22:27.570
Neither do I.

1366
01:22:27.653 --> 01:22:29.075
I know, sweetie pie.

1367
01:22:29.154 --> 01:22:31.452
But you can pay me
in government information.


1368
01:22:31.531 --> 01:22:32.908
All of you.

1369
01:22:34.493 --> 01:22:36.495
Except you, Wadsworth.

1370
01:22:36.578 --> 01:22:38.125
You as a mere butler

1371
01:22:38.205 --> 01:22:40.708
have no access to government secrets.

1372
01:22:40.791 --> 01:22:44.512
So, I'm afraid your moment has come.

1373
01:22:44.586 --> 01:22:46.338
Not so fast, Miss Scarlet.

1374
01:22:46.421 --> 01:22:47.798
I do have a secret or two.

1375
01:22:47.881 --> 01:22:50.100
- Yeah? Such as?
- The game's up, Scarlet.


1376
01:22:50.175 --> 01:22:51.927
There are no more bullets
left in that gun.


1377
01:22:52.010 --> 01:22:54.263
Come on. You don't think
I'm gonna fall for that old trick.


1378
01:22:54.346 --> 01:22:55.518
It's not a trick.

1379
01:22:55.597 --> 01:22:57.850
There was one shot at Mr. Boddy in
the study, two for the chandelier,


1380
01:22:57.933 --> 01:23:00.106
two at the lounge door,
and one for the singing telegram.


1381
01:23:00.185 --> 01:23:02.984
- That's not six.
- One plus two plus two plus one.


1382
01:23:03.105 --> 01:23:05.449
- uh. It was only one shot
that got the chandelier.


1383
01:23:05.524 --> 01:23:07.117
That's one plus two plus one plus one.

1384
01:23:07.192 --> 01:23:09.536
Even if you're right, that'll be
one plus one plus two plus one.


1385
01:23:09.611 --> 01:23:11.534
Not one plus two plus one plus one.

1386
01:23:11.613 --> 01:23:14.913
Okay, fine, one plus two plus one...
Shut up!


1387
01:23:15.242 --> 01:23:17.586
Point is there's one bullet left
in this gun.


1388
01:23:17.661 --> 01:23:19.584
And guess who's getting it?

1389
01:23:19.663 --> 01:23:22.416
Om

1390
01:23:30.382 --> 01:23:32.009
I'm only a guest.

1391
01:23:35.095 --> 01:23:36.517
Where's the chief?

1392
01:23:37.889 --> 01:23:39.937
Wadsworth, well done.

1393
01:23:40.016 --> 01:23:42.439
I did warn you, my dear.

1394
01:23:42.519 --> 01:23:45.443
Mr. Hoover is an expert on Armageddon.

1395
01:23:45.522 --> 01:23:48.947
Wadsworth. Don't hate me
for trying to shoot you.


1396
01:23:49.025 --> 01:23:50.823
Frankly, Scarlet, 
I don't give a damn.

1397
01:23:50.902 --> 01:23:54.076
As I was trying to tell you, there are
no bullets left in this gun, you see?


1398
01:23:58.201 --> 01:23:59.953
One plus two...

1399
01:24:00.036 --> 01:24:01.538
Plus one...

1400
01:24:01.621 --> 01:24:03.089
Plus two...

1401
01:24:03.165 --> 01:24:05.338
Plus one is...

1402
01:24:20.348 --> 01:24:22.976
In the dark, the murderer
ran across the hall to the study,


1403
01:24:23.059 --> 01:24:24.732
picked up the rope and the lead pipe,

1404
01:24:24.811 --> 01:24:26.438
ran to the billiard room,

1405
01:24:26.521 --> 01:24:28.615
strangled Yvette.

1406
01:24:29.900 --> 01:24:32.995
Ran to the library, hit the cop
on the head with the lead pipe.


1407
01:24:33.069 --> 01:24:36.039
Then, coming out of the library, the
doorbell rang. It was a singing telegram.


1408
01:24:36.114 --> 01:24:38.116
The murderer picked up the gun
where Yvette dropped it,


1409
01:24:38.200 --> 01:24:39.622
ran to the door, opened it,

1410
01:24:39.701 --> 01:24:41.453
recognized the girl
from her photograph, shot her,


1411
01:24:41.536 --> 01:24:43.413
and then ran back to the cellar.

1412
01:24:43.497 --> 01:24:45.249
- The cellar!
- Yes.


1413
01:24:45.332 --> 01:24:47.460
But Colonel Mustard
wasn't in the cellar.


1414
01:24:47.542 --> 01:24:50.887
No, but you were.

1415
01:24:51.963 --> 01:24:53.010
So?

1416
01:24:53.089 --> 01:24:54.557
You murdered them all.

1417
01:24:54.633 --> 01:24:55.930
You were the person who was missing

1418
01:24:56.009 --> 01:24:57.386
when the cook and Mr. Boddy
were murdered,


1419
01:24:57.469 --> 01:24:59.471
and the cook used to be your cook.

1420
01:24:59.554 --> 01:25:02.728
Don't you remember your fatal mistake?

1421
01:25:02.891 --> 01:25:04.359
You told us at dinner

1422
01:25:04.434 --> 01:25:07.028
that we were eating
one of your favorite recipes,


1423
01:25:07.103 --> 01:25:10.482
and monkey's brains,
though popular in Cantonese cuisine,


1424
01:25:10.565 --> 01:25:12.818
are not often to be found
in Washington, D.C.


1425
01:25:12.901 --> 01:25:15.324
Is that what we ate?

1426
01:25:15.403 --> 01:25:17.497
Why would I have murdered
all the others?


1427
01:25:17.572 --> 01:25:19.950
Obviously, in case Mr. Boddy
had told them about you.


1428
01:25:20.033 --> 01:25:22.832
So this all had nothing to do
with the disappearing nuclear physicist


1429
01:25:22.911 --> 01:25:24.663
and Colonel Mustard's work
on the new fusion bomb.


1430
01:25:24.746 --> 01:25:26.794
No. Communism was just a red herring.

1431
01:25:26.873 --> 01:25:29.752
Mrs. Peacock did it all.

1432
01:25:29.835 --> 01:25:31.178
There's no proof.

1433
01:25:31.253 --> 01:25:33.176
Well, the gun is missing.

1434
01:25:33.255 --> 01:25:35.223
Gentlemen, turn out your pockets.

1435
01:25:35.298 --> 01:25:37.050
Ladies, empty your purses.

1436
01:25:37.133 --> 01:25:39.431
Whoever has the gun

1437
01:25:39.511 --> 01:25:41.354
- is the murderer.
- Very well.


1438
01:25:43.431 --> 01:25:46.401
What do you propose to do about it?

1439
01:25:46.476 --> 01:25:48.399
Nothing.

1440
01:25:48.478 --> 01:25:50.196
- Nothing?
- Nothing at all.


1441
01:25:50.397 --> 01:25:52.240
I don't approve of murder,

1442
01:25:52.315 --> 01:25:54.568
but it seems to me you've done
the world a public service


1443
01:25:54.651 --> 01:25:57.871
by ridding it of an appalling blackmailer
and his disgusting informers.


1444
01:25:57.946 --> 01:26:00.244
But the police will be here any minute.
What happens then?


1445
01:26:00.323 --> 01:26:01.825
Why should the police come?

1446
01:26:01.908 --> 01:26:03.125
Nobody's called them.

1447
01:26:03.201 --> 01:26:05.545
- You mean...
- That's right.


1448
01:26:06.454 --> 01:26:10.379
Now I suggest that we stack
the bodies in the cellar,


1449
01:26:10.458 --> 01:26:12.961
lock it, leave quietly one at a time,

1450
01:26:13.044 --> 01:26:15.888
and pretend that none of this
has ever happened.


1451
01:26:15.964 --> 01:26:17.887
Great idea.

1452
01:26:17.966 --> 01:26:20.685
I'll leave first, if you don't mind.

1453
01:26:22.220 --> 01:26:23.221
Be my guest.

1454
01:26:23.805 --> 01:26:27.230
In fact, I think we all owe you
a vote of thanks.


1455
01:26:29.144 --> 01:26:31.397
For she's a jolly good fellow.

1456
01:26:31.479 --> 01:26:37.612
For she's a jolly good fellow.

1457
01:26:37.694 --> 01:26:44.703
Which nobody can deny.

1458
01:26:44.784 --> 01:26:48.914
For she's a jolly good fellow.

1459
01:26:48.997 --> 01:26:50.920
For she's a jolly...

1460
01:26:50.999 --> 01:26:53.593
I told you I didn't do it.

1461
01:26:53.668 --> 01:26:55.545
What if the authorities find out
what happened?


1462
01:26:55.629 --> 01:26:57.427
The FBI will take care of that.

1463
01:26:57.505 --> 01:26:59.758
- You mean...
- My call from Mr. Hoover.


1464
01:26:59.841 --> 01:27:01.309
I work for him of course.

1465
01:27:01.384 --> 01:27:03.512
How else could I have known
everything about you all?


1466
01:27:03.678 --> 01:27:05.680
There's still one thing
I don't understand.


1467
01:27:05.764 --> 01:27:07.141
One thing?

1468
01:27:07.223 --> 01:27:09.976
Who was Mrs. Peacock
taking bribes from?


1469
01:27:10.060 --> 01:27:11.357
A foreign power.

1470
01:27:11.436 --> 01:27:13.564
Her husband, the senator,
has influence over defense contracts.


1471
01:27:13.855 --> 01:27:14.981
Is there gonna be a cover-up?

1472
01:27:15.065 --> 01:27:18.444
Isn't that in the public interest?
What could be gained by exposure?


1473
01:27:18.526 --> 01:27:21.405
Does the FBI have a habit
of cleaning up after multiple murder?


1474
01:27:21.488 --> 01:27:24.037
Yes. Why do you think
it's run by a man called Hoover?


1475
01:27:30.246 --> 01:27:31.714
Mrs. Peacock.

1476
01:27:35.585 --> 01:27:36.802
How did you know my name?

1477
01:27:36.878 --> 01:27:39.631
The kingdom of heaven is at hand.

1478
01:27:40.924 --> 01:27:42.801
Okay, take her away.

1479
01:27:44.970 --> 01:27:46.347
Take your hands off me!

1480
01:27:46.972 --> 01:27:48.849
I'm a senator's wife!

1481
01:27:51.226 --> 01:27:52.944
Wadsworth, we got her.

1482
01:27:53.019 --> 01:27:55.488
You see, it's like the Mounties.

1483
01:27:55.563 --> 01:27:57.486
We always get our man.

1484
01:27:57.565 --> 01:27:59.442
Mrs. Peacock was a man?

1485
01:28:01.361 --> 01:28:04.160
Would anyone care for fruit or dessert?

1486
01:28:17.252 --> 01:28:19.675
Sorry, didn't mean to frighten anyone.

1487
01:28:19.754 --> 01:28:21.256
You're a bit late for that!

1488
01:28:21.339 --> 01:28:23.216
Then there were three more murders.

1489
01:28:23.299 --> 01:28:24.676
- Who did it?
- Who did it?


1490
01:28:24.759 --> 01:28:28.059
Let's consider each murder one by one.

1491
01:28:28.138 --> 01:28:31.062
Professor Plum.
You knew Mr. Boddy was still alive.


1492
01:28:31.141 --> 01:28:33.564
Even psychiatrists
can tell the difference


1493
01:28:33.643 --> 01:28:35.896
between patients who are alive or dead.

1494
01:28:35.979 --> 01:28:38.107
You fired the gun in the dark,
and missed,


1495
01:28:38.189 --> 01:28:40.157
so you pretended he was dead

1496
01:28:40.233 --> 01:28:43.362
that's how you were able
to kill him later, unobserved.


1497
01:28:43.445 --> 01:28:46.164
That's right. He was the missing
person in the kitchen


1498
01:28:46.239 --> 01:28:47.365
after we found the cook dead.

1499
01:28:47.449 --> 01:28:50.293
But he was with us in the billiard room
when we found Yvette screaming.


1500
01:28:50.368 --> 01:28:52.166
If that's when the cook was killed,
how did he do it?


1501
01:28:52.245 --> 01:28:53.212
I didn't!

1502
01:28:53.288 --> 01:28:55.711
You don't expect us to believe that,
do you?


1503
01:28:55.790 --> 01:28:58.043
I expect you to believe it.
You killed the cook,


1504
01:28:58.168 --> 01:29:01.468
she used to be your cook,
and she informed on you to Mr. Boddy.


1505
01:29:01.546 --> 01:29:03.640
You made one fatal mistake.

1506
01:29:03.715 --> 01:29:06.685
Sitting here at dinner,
Mrs. Peacock told us she was eating


1507
01:29:06.760 --> 01:29:09.263
one of her favorite recipes,

1508
01:29:09.345 --> 01:29:12.815
and monkey's brains,
though popular in Cantonese cuisine,


1509
01:29:12.891 --> 01:29:16.771
are not often to be found
in Washington, D.C.


1510
01:29:16.853 --> 01:29:20.232
Colonel Mustard, when we saw
the motorist at the front door,


1511
01:29:20.315 --> 01:29:22.909
you took the key to the weapons
cupboard out of my pocket,


1512
01:29:22.984 --> 01:29:24.702
then you suggested that we all split up.

1513
01:29:24.778 --> 01:29:26.371
You separated from Miss Scarlet,

1514
01:29:26.446 --> 01:29:30.167
crossed the hall,
opened the cupboard, took the wrench,


1515
01:29:30.241 --> 01:29:32.869
ran to the conservatory, entered the
lounge through the secret passage,


1516
01:29:32.952 --> 01:29:34.579
killed the motorist
with a blow on the head,


1517
01:29:34.662 --> 01:29:36.164
like that!

1518
01:29:38.333 --> 01:29:39.755
This is incredible.

1519
01:29:39.834 --> 01:29:42.053
Not so incredible
as what happened next.


1520
01:29:42.128 --> 01:29:43.505
After we all split up again,

1521
01:29:43.588 --> 01:29:46.842
I went upstairs with you,
yes, you, Mrs. White.


1522
01:29:46.966 --> 01:29:50.345
And while I was in the master bedroom,

1523
01:29:50.512 --> 01:29:54.233
you hurried downstairs
and turned off the electricity,


1524
01:29:54.307 --> 01:29:57.857
got the rope from the open cupboard,
and throttled Yvette.


1525
01:29:57.936 --> 01:30:00.280
Your were jealous that your husband
was shtupping Yvette.


1526
01:30:00.355 --> 01:30:02.232
That's why you killed him, too.

1527
01:30:02.315 --> 01:30:03.407
Yes.

1528
01:30:06.528 --> 01:30:09.452
Yes, I did it. 
I killed Yvette.

1529
01:30:09.531 --> 01:30:12.956
I hated her so much,

1530
01:30:13.034 --> 01:30:16.459
it flames,

1531
01:30:16.538 --> 01:30:19.291
flames on the side of my face,

1532
01:30:19.374 --> 01:30:22.924
breathing, heaving breaths,

1533
01:30:23.002 --> 01:30:24.254
heaving...

1534
01:30:24.337 --> 01:30:25.509
But while we were in the billiard room,

1535
01:30:25.588 --> 01:30:27.966
Miss Scarlet seized the opportunity
and under cover of darkness,


1536
01:30:28.049 --> 01:30:31.349
crossed to the library, where she hit
the cop, whom she'd been bribing,


1537
01:30:31.427 --> 01:30:32.849
on the head with a lead pipe.

1538
01:30:32.929 --> 01:30:34.727
True or false?

1539
01:30:34.806 --> 01:30:37.810
True. Who are you, Perry Mason?

1540
01:30:37.892 --> 01:30:40.190
So, it must have been Mr. Green
who shot the singing telegram.


1541
01:30:40.270 --> 01:30:41.362
I didn't do it!

1542
01:30:41.437 --> 01:30:42.654
Well there's nobody else left.

1543
01:30:42.730 --> 01:30:44.152
But I didn't do it!

1544
01:30:44.232 --> 01:30:48.237
The gun is missing.
Whoever's got the gun, shot the girl.


1545
01:30:48.528 --> 01:30:49.700
I shot her.

1546
01:30:50.029 --> 01:30:51.076
_You .?
'You?


1547
01:30:52.574 --> 01:30:54.167
So, it was you.

1548
01:30:54.242 --> 01:30:55.539
I was going to expose you.

1549
01:30:55.618 --> 01:30:57.871
I know. So I choose to expose myself.

1550
01:30:57.954 --> 01:30:59.877
Please. There are ladies present.

1551
01:30:59.956 --> 01:31:01.833
You thought Mr. Boddy was dead.
But why?


1552
01:31:01.916 --> 01:31:04.840
None of you even met him till tonight.

1553
01:31:05.461 --> 01:31:07.088
You're Mr. Boddy!

1554
01:31:08.715 --> 01:31:10.012
Wait a minute!

1555
01:31:10.091 --> 01:31:11.764
SO who did I kill?

1556
01:31:11.843 --> 01:31:13.265
My butler.

1557
01:31:13.344 --> 01:31:15.017
Shucks.

1558
01:31:16.431 --> 01:31:18.479
He was expendable, like all of you.

1559
01:31:18.558 --> 01:31:22.608
I'm grateful to you all for disposing
of my network of spies and informers.


1560
01:31:22.687 --> 01:31:26.032
Saved me a lot of trouble.
Now there's no evidence against me.


1561
01:31:26.107 --> 01:31:27.700
This all has nothing to do

1562
01:31:27.775 --> 01:31:30.028
with my disappearing
nuclear physicist husband


1563
01:31:30.111 --> 01:31:33.331
or Colonel Mustard's work
with the new, top secret fusion bomb?


1564
01:31:33.406 --> 01:31:34.453
No.

1565
01:31:34.532 --> 01:31:36.785
Communism was just a red herring.

1566
01:31:38.786 --> 01:31:41.005
The police will be here any minute.

1567
01:31:41.080 --> 01:31:43.503
You'll never get away with this,
any of you.


1568
01:31:43.583 --> 01:31:46.302
Why should the police come?
Nobody's called them.


1569
01:31:46.377 --> 01:31:47.378
You mean...

1570
01:31:47.462 --> 01:31:49.089
My God. Of course!

1571
01:31:49.172 --> 01:31:51.266
So why shouldn't we get away with it?

1572
01:31:51.341 --> 01:31:53.139
We'll stack the bodies in the cellar,
lock it,


1573
01:31:53.218 --> 01:31:55.061
leave quietly, one at a time,

1574
01:31:55.136 --> 01:31:56.809
and forget that any of this
ever happened.


1575
01:31:57.055 --> 01:32:00.150
And you'll just go on blackmailing us all.

1576
01:32:00.225 --> 01:32:02.148
Of course. Why not?

1577
01:32:02.268 --> 01:32:03.645
I'll tell you why not.

1578
01:32:05.271 --> 01:32:06.272
Aah!

1579
01:32:06.356 --> 01:32:08.779
Good shot, Green.

1580
01:32:20.828 --> 01:32:23.172
Very good.

1581
01:32:31.172 --> 01:32:32.970
Are you a cop?

1582
01:32:33.049 --> 01:32:35.051
- No. I'm a plant.
- Plant?


1583
01:32:35.134 --> 01:32:36.807
I thought men like you
were usually called a fruit.


1584
01:32:36.886 --> 01:32:38.354
Very funny.

1585
01:32:38.429 --> 01:32:42.059
FBI. That phone call
from J. Edgar Hoover was for me.


1586
01:32:44.352 --> 01:32:47.151
I told you I didn't do it.

1587
01:32:52.735 --> 01:32:54.362
All right, who done it?

1588
01:32:54.445 --> 01:32:56.288
- They... She did...
- That lady... He...


1589
01:32:56.364 --> 01:32:58.287
- This one...
- Gentlemen...


1590
01:32:58.366 --> 01:32:59.959
They all did it!

1591
01:33:01.077 --> 01:33:04.297
But if you want to know
who killed Mr. Boddy,


1592
01:33:04.372 --> 01:33:07.546
I did, in the hall, with the revolver.

1593
01:33:08.835 --> 01:33:10.257
Okay, Chief, take them away.

1594
01:33:10.795 --> 01:33:13.639
I'm gonna go home
and sleep with my wife.